{
  "texts": [
    "The average of the squared differences between predicted and actual values.",
    "It penalizes larger errors more heavily.",
    "where, M and N are the dimensions of the image.",
    "Original (i,j) and Denoised (i,j) are the pixel values at position (i, j) in the original and denoised images respectively.",
    "PSNR is commonly used to measure the quality of restored images."
